<p>The second YOCLK was constructed to operate at a frequency of ~1.18Hz. R1 was a1kÎ© resistor, R2 was a 150kÎ© resistor, and C1 was a4.7ÂµF electrolytic capacitor. Additionally, a 0.1ÂµF capacitor was connected to pin 5 which was subsequently connected to ground to reduce noise, and pin 4 was connected to Vs +. Once the components were soldered onto the circuit board, the circuit had a frequency of 1.179Hz and a duty cycle of 52.60%.</p>

